+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_015fet5ERgHKmZT9QcpHJQJu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013BR5MYSJaVr7ybFQ5yTfZC","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-versioned-document-store-design.md","content":"# Versioned Document Store — Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### File Structure\n- `src/index.ts` — Exports `DocumentStore` class, types (`Version`, `MergeResult`, `Conflict`)\n- `src/types.ts` — Shared type definitions\n- `src/merge.ts` — Three-way structural merge algorithm\n- `src/store.ts` — Core `DocumentStore` class implementation\n\n### Internal Data Model\n\n```typescript\n// Per-document state within a branch\ninterface DocState {\n  content: object;       // current content (deep-cloned on store/retrieve)\n  versions: Version[];   // chronological version history\n  deleted: boolean;      // soft-delete flag for merge tracking\n}\n\n// Per-branch state\ninterface BranchState {\n  documents: Map<string, DocState>;\n  // Snapshot of document contents at the point this branch forked\n  forkBase: Map<string, object | null>;  // null = didn't exist at fork time\n  parentBranch: string | null;           // which branch this was forked from\n}\n```\n\n- `main` branch is created on construction with empty state and no parent.\n- `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` deep-clones the source branch's document map, and records a `forkBase` snapshot of every document's current content.\n- Version IDs: monotonic counter (`v1`, `v2`, ...) shared across all branches.\n\n### CRUD Operations\n\nAll operate on the current branch's `BranchState.documents`:\n- **create**: Throw if id exists and not deleted. Add DocState, push version.\n- **get**: Throw if not found or deleted. Return `structuredClone(content)`.\n- **update**: Throw if not found or deleted. Replace content, push version.\n- **delete**: Throw if not found or deleted. Set `deleted: true`.\n\n### Three-Way Merge Algorithm (`merge.ts`)\n\n1. Collect all document IDs across: source branch docs, target branch docs, and forkBase.\n2. For each document ID, determine base/ours/theirs states:\n   - **base**: forkBase snapshot (null if didn't exist)\n   - **ours**: current branch's current state\n   - **theirs**: source branch's current state\n3. Categorize:\n   - Only one side changed → take that side's value (auto-merge)\n   - Both changed same way → no conflict\n   - Both changed differently → conflict\n4. For documents present on both sides, do recursive field-by-field merge:\n   - Walk object keys at each nesting level\n   - Build dot-separated path for conflict reporting\n   - For primitive values: compare base→ours and base→theirs\n   - For nested objects: recurse\n   - For arrays: treat as atomic values (compare whole array)\n5. Return `MergeResult` with merged contents, conflicts list, and `applied` flag.\n6. If no conflicts, apply merged state to current branch.\n\n### Deep Cloning\n\nUse `structuredClone()` for all clone operations (store and retrieve).\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- Merging a branch with itself: no-op\n- Document created on source but not base: add to merged\n- Document deleted on one side, unchanged on other: apply delete\n- Document deleted on one side, modified on other: conflict\n- Empty merge (no changes): fast-forward, `applied: true`, empty merged/conflicts\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":821,"cache_read_input_tokens":24035,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":821},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b5ca98-824f-463d-afb8-e082a117a13e","uuid":"8ba72560-3271-43f1-990f-f950dd43d1aa"}
