+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013YTEjYVfnFY4qqJJNuWp6c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Versioned Document Store — Design\n     2→\n     3→## Architecture\n     4→\n     5→### File Structure\n     6→- `src/index.ts` — Exports `DocumentStore` class, types (`Version`, `MergeResult`, `Conflict`)\n     7→- `src/types.ts` — Shared type definitions\n     8→- `src/merge.ts` — Three-way structural merge algorithm\n     9→- `src/store.ts` — Core `DocumentStore` class implementation\n    10→\n    11→### Internal Data Model\n    12→\n    13→```typescript\n    14→// Per-document state within a branch\n    15→interface DocState {\n    16→  content: object;       // current content (deep-cloned on store/retrieve)\n    17→  versions: Version[];   // chronological version history\n    18→  deleted: boolean;      // soft-delete flag for merge tracking\n    19→}\n    20→\n    21→// Per-branch state\n    22→interface BranchState {\n    23→  documents: Map<string, DocState>;\n    24→  // Snapshot of document contents at the point this branch forked\n    25→  forkBase: Map<string, object | null>;  // null = didn't exist at fork time\n    26→  parentBranch: string | null;           // which branch this was forked from\n    27→}\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→- `main` branch is created on construction with empty state and no parent.\n    31→- `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` deep-clones the source branch's document map, and records a `forkBase` snapshot of every document's current content.\n    32→- Version IDs: monotonic counter (`v1`, `v2`, ...) shared across all branches.\n    33→\n    34→### CRUD Operations\n    35→\n    36→All operate on the current branch's `BranchState.documents`:\n    37→- **create**: Throw if id exists and not deleted. Add DocState, push version.\n    38→- **get**: Throw if not found or deleted. Return `structuredClone(content)`.\n    39→- **update**: Throw if not found or deleted. Replace content, push version.\n    40→- **delete**: Throw if not found or deleted. Set `deleted: true`.\n    41→\n    42→### Three-Way Merge Algorithm (`merge.ts`)\n    43→\n    44→1. Collect all document IDs across: source branch docs, target branch docs, and forkBase.\n    45→2. For each document ID, determine base/ours/theirs states:\n    46→   - **base**: forkBase snapshot (null if didn't exist)\n    47→   - **ours**: current branch's current state\n    48→   - **theirs**: source branch's current state\n    49→3. Categorize:\n    50→   - Only one side changed → take that side's value (auto-merge)\n    51→   - Both changed same way → no conflict\n    52→   - Both changed differently → conflict\n    53→4. For documents present on both sides, do recursive field-by-field merge:\n    54→   - Walk object keys at each nesting level\n    55→   - Build dot-separated path for conflict reporting\n    56→   - For primitive values: compare base→ours and base→theirs\n    57→   - For nested objects: recurse\n    58→   - For arrays: treat as atomic values (compare whole array)\n    59→5. Return `MergeResult` with merged contents, conflicts list, and `applied` flag.\n    60→6. If no conflicts, apply merged state to current branch.\n    61→\n    62→### Deep Cloning\n    63→\n    64→Use `structuredClone()` for all clone operations (store and retrieve).\n    65→\n    66→### Edge Cases\n    67→\n    68→- Merging a branch with itself: no-op\n    69→- Document created on source but not base: add to merged\n    70→- Document deleted on one side, unchanged on other: apply delete\n    71→- Document deleted on one side, modified on other: conflict\n    72→- Empty merge (no changes): fast-forward, `applied: true`, empty merged/conflicts\n    73→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"21b5ca98-824f-463d-afb8-e082a117a13e","uuid":"e30ff1fc-c741-42cc-ac9d-39f707420629","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-versioned-document-store-design.md","content":"# Versioned Document Store — Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### File Structure\n- `src/index.ts` — Exports `DocumentStore` class, types (`Version`, `MergeResult`, `Conflict`)\n- `src/types.ts` — Shared type definitions\n- `src/merge.ts` — Three-way structural merge algorithm\n- `src/store.ts` — Core `DocumentStore` class implementation\n\n### Internal Data Model\n\n```typescript\n// Per-document state within a branch\ninterface DocState {\n  content: object;       // current content (deep-cloned on store/retrieve)\n  versions: Version[];   // chronological version history\n  deleted: boolean;      // soft-delete flag for merge tracking\n}\n\n// Per-branch state\ninterface BranchState {\n  documents: Map<string, DocState>;\n  // Snapshot of document contents at the point this branch forked\n  forkBase: Map<string, object | null>;  // null = didn't exist at fork time\n  parentBranch: string | null;           // which branch this was forked from\n}\n```\n\n- `main` branch is created on construction with empty state and no parent.\n- `createBranch(name, fromBranch?)` deep-clones the source branch's document map, and records a `forkBase` snapshot of every document's current content.\n- Version IDs: monotonic counter (`v1`, `v2`, ...) shared across all branches.\n\n### CRUD Operations\n\nAll operate on the current branch's `BranchState.documents`:\n- **create**: Throw if id exists and not deleted. Add DocState, push version.\n- **get**: Throw if not found or deleted. Return `structuredClone(content)`.\n- **update**: Throw if not found or deleted. Replace content, push version.\n- **delete**: Throw if not found or deleted. Set `deleted: true`.\n\n### Three-Way Merge Algorithm (`merge.ts`)\n\n1. Collect all document IDs across: source branch docs, target branch docs, and forkBase.\n2. For each document ID, determine base/ours/theirs states:\n   - **base**: forkBase snapshot (null if didn't exist)\n   - **ours**: current branch's current state\n   - **theirs**: source branch's current state\n3. Categorize:\n   - Only one side changed → take that side's value (auto-merge)\n   - Both changed same way → no conflict\n   - Both changed differently → conflict\n4. For documents present on both sides, do recursive field-by-field merge:\n   - Walk object keys at each nesting level\n   - Build dot-separated path for conflict reporting\n   - For primitive values: compare base→ours and base→theirs\n   - For nested objects: recurse\n   - For arrays: treat as atomic values (compare whole array)\n5. Return `MergeResult` with merged contents, conflicts list, and `applied` flag.\n6. If no conflicts, apply merged state to current branch.\n\n### Deep Cloning\n\nUse `structuredClone()` for all clone operations (store and retrieve).\n\n### Edge Cases\n\n- Merging a branch with itself: no-op\n- Document created on source but not base: add to merged\n- Document deleted on one side, unchanged on other: apply delete\n- Document deleted on one side, modified on other: conflict\n- Empty merge (no changes): fast-forward, `applied: true`, empty merged/conflicts\n","numLines":73,"startLine":1,"totalLines":73}}}
